                  </persName>
            . I am a constable, and received the prisoner in charge.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I am a foreigner, and was out of employ. I was coming through Fleet-street, and saw a person running; he dropped the print; I took it up almost immediately afterwards; this gentleman found me in Fleet-market, and on asking what I was doing with it, I, of course, knowing it was not my own, surrendered it to him. <rs id="t18280529-4-verdict17" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280529-4-verdict17" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-4-verdict17" type="verdictSubcategory" value="lesserOffence"></interp>
               GUILTY. Aged 35. Of stealing only
            </rs>. - <rs id="t18280529-4-punish18" type="punishmentDescription">
